attributes.documentation:
@title Market Oracle
 * @dev Provides the exchange rate and volume data onchain using data from a whitelisted
     set of market source contracts.
     Exchange rate is the TOKEN:TARGET rate.
     Volume is a 24 hour trading volume in Token volume.
attributes.name: MarketOracle
getPriceAnd24HourVolume

attributes.documentation:
@dev Adds a market source to the whitelist.
@param source Address of the MarketSource.
attributes.name: addSource

attributes.documentation:
@dev Removes the provided market source from the whitelist.
@param source Address of the MarketSource.
attributes.name: removeSource

attributes.documentation:
@dev Expunges from the whitelist any MarketSource whose associated contracts have been
     destructed.
attributes.name: removeDestructedSources

attributes.documentation: @return The number of market sources in the whitelist.
attributes.name: whitelistSize

attributes.documentation:
@dev Checks if a contract has been destructed.
@param contractAddress Address of the contract.
attributes.name: isContractDestructed

attributes.documentation: @param index Index of the MarketSource to be removed from the whitelist.
attributes.name: removeSourceAtIndex
MarketSource
reportRate

attributes.documentation:
@return Most recently reported market information.
        isFresh: Is true if the last report is within the expiration window and
                 false if the report has expired.
        exchangeRate: The average exchange rate over the last reported 24 hours
                      of TOKEN:TARGET.
                      18 decimal fixed point number.
        volume24hrs:  The trade volume of last 24 hours reported in Token volume.
                      18 decimal fixed point number.
attributes.name: getReport

attributes.documentation:
@title Destructible
@dev Base contract that can be destroyed by owner. All funds in contract will be sent to the owner.
attributes.name: Destructible

attributes.documentation: @dev Transfers the current balance to the owner and terminates the contract.
attributes.name: destroy

attributes.documentation:
@title SafeMath
@dev Math operations with safety checks that throw on error
attributes.name: SafeMath

attributes.documentation: @dev Multiplies two numbers, throws on overflow.
attributes.name: mul

attributes.documentation: @dev Integer division of two numbers, truncating the quotient.
attributes.name: div

attributes.documentation: @dev Subtracts two numbers, throws on overflow (i.e. if subtrahend is greater than minuend).
attributes.name: sub

attributes.documentation: @dev Adds two numbers, throws on overflow.
attributes.name: add
Ownable

attributes.documentation:
@dev The Ownable constructor sets the original `owner` of the contract to the sender
account.
@dev Throws if called by any account other than the owner.
attributes.name: onlyOwner

attributes.documentation: @dev Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.
attributes.name: renounceOwnership

attributes.documentation:
@dev Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.
@param _newOwner The address to transfer ownership to.
attributes.name: transferOwnership

attributes.documentation:
@dev Transfers control of the contract to a newOwner.
@param _newOwner The address to transfer ownership to.
